FBIS4-40169 "drsov115_a_94022" FBIS-SOV-94-115 Daily Report 14 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Foreign Ministry Official on EC Entry Foreign Ministry Official on EC Entry LD1406210994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2036 GMT 14 Jun 94 LD1406210994 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Dmitriy Gorokhov] [Text] Moscow June 14 TASS -- A Russian Foreign Ministry's official said Russia is likely to join the European Council in a few months. "We presume that Russia might become a member of the European Council within the next six months, and not later than next spring", Galina Sidorova, a spokeswoman for Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, told reporters on Tuesday. According to Sidorova, earlier, Russia's entering the EC was conditioned on the adoption of a new constitution. Now Russia has its new constitution adopted. And this "enables her to bid for an equal place among the members of the European Council", she said.
